title: Average retail price for butter in Canada 2015 to 2019
summary: This grouped bar chart represents Average retail price in CAD on the Y-axis. And, its value throughout 12 Months for 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019.
Over the 12 Months, the Average retail price in CAD for 2017 have been reduced whereas increased for 2016.
Out of all 5 groups, 2019 had the highest Average retail price in CAD in Month Jul and 2015 had the lowest Average retail price in CAD in Month Jul.
Among all the Months, 2017 had the highest Average retail price in CAD 494.0 in Month Jun and lowest value 49.0 in Month Mar.
